make decision with incomplete information?
1.Find out the situation. Understand the issues from multiple perspectives.
2. Think of the best and worst that will happen.
3.Discuss with your close connections to create appropriate alternatives.
4. Choose the decision that is possible and feasible to execute with limited risk and maximum returns.
5. Obtain feedback to improve your decisions in the future.

https://trainingmag.com/making-decisions-limited-and-imperfect-information/

How to resolve conflict
1. listen from both parties
2. Define the problem and determine the underlying need
3. Find common areas of agreement, no matter how small
4. Find solutions to satisfy needs:
5. Determine follow-up you will take to monitor actions.
6. Determine what you'll do if the conflict goes unresolved.

https://hr.berkeley.edu/hr-network/central-guide-managing-hr/managing-hr/interaction/conflict/resolving

How to handle unexcited projects
1. Focus on small, meaningful wins.
2. Make a game out of keeping the project aligned with business goals

https://www.liquidplanner.com/blog/8-ways-stay-motivated-when-youre-working-on-the-never-ending-project-from-hell/ 


What if coworker took you credit?
1. Calm down. you are not at your best with anger? may harm the team?
2. Think of why this could happen? Unintentional?
3. Remedy the situation
4. How to prevent it from happening

https://hbr.org/2015/04/how-to-respond-when-someone-takes-credit-for-your-work

Work with Someone Who Isn’t a Team Player?
1. Don’t jump to conclusions 
2. Start a dialogue
3. Invite them in. out to coffee or lunch or etc
4. Revisit the team’s mission. indicating that something is off with the group

5. Clarify team members’ roles. “Don’t assume everybody knows exactly what their contribution is supposed to be,”

6. Identify new opportunities to motivate.
A team member may not only distance themselves because they’re confused; they could find the work they’ve been assigned to be pointless and boring

https://hbr.org/2017/04/how-to-work-with-someone-who-isnt-a-team-player